notesStmt.note: Scribe for first work "per Johannem de prawnec" [i.e., Brauneck] at Donauwörth, 1470 (f. 124r).
(1st work): Expliciunt sermones de avaritia sive usuris per...Johannes Goldner decretorum doctorem...(f. 124r).
(2nd work): Explicit sermo...magistri Nicolai Dinkelspuhel (f. 143r); Sermon published from other manuscripts by H. Menhardt.
(5th work): Incipiunt tres puncti essenciales religionis Xristianae...(f. 146r).
(10th work): attributed to Nicolaus von Dinkelsbühl (Zacour-Hirsch).

(14th work): Explicit tractatus cum registro suo continenti xlv articulos erroreos sive heretices Johannis Wickleph. Editus per [?] doctorem sacrae theologiae magistrum Stansilaum felicis [?] de Znoyma.
"Elisabeth sancte in claustro me bibliotheca possideat" (inside lower cover).

msContents.summary: Miscellany bound in the late 15th century, with contemporary table of contents for the second half of the text (f. 257v), and paper index tabs on outer margins to locate works. Many works include dates but are probably later copies.

supportDesc.extent: 257 leaves : 203 x 156 (147 x 102) mm. bound to 216 x 165 mm

collation.p: Paper, 257; 1-12¹², 13¹⁴ (-14), 14-16¹², 17-20¹⁶; [1-145], 1-23, [i], 24-32, 34-63, 63-109, [i]; contemporary foliation in ink, upper center recto; modern foliation in pencil, upper right recto.

layoutDesc.layout: Written in 27-37 long lines; ruled in lead.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a German Gothic script by several hands.

decoDesc.decoNote: Decorated initials in black and red (f. 170r, 193v); rubricated headings, capitals, initials, paragraph marks, and manicules.

binding.p: Contemporary stamped leather over wooden boards, with remains of clasp.

origin.p: Written in Bohemia in the 15th century (Zacour-Hirsch).

history.provenance: Provenance: Poor Clares at Brixen (Tyrol), "Liber iste Cenobii est Clarissarum Brixine commorancium" (inside upper cover).
